3. How would you refactor a piece of code to use Lambda expressions?
Answer:
If you have an anonymous class like:
Runnable r = new Runnable() {
    public void run() {
        System.out.println("Running...");
    }
};
It can be refactored using a lambda expression:
Runnable r = () -> System.out.println("Running...");

